he opposite to be true: sanctions strengthened the Iranian state, impoverished its population, increased state repression, and escalated Iran's military posture toward the U.S. and its allies in the region. Instead of offering an 'alternative to war,' sanctions have become a cause of war. Consequently, How Sanctions Work reveals how necessary it is to understand how sanctions really work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic sanctionszIran2DLC. 0aEconomic sanctionszIran. 0aEconomic sanctions, AmericanzIran2DLC. 0aEconomic sanctions, AmericanzIran. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh  aIran.  aMiddle East.  aUS foreign policy.  asanctions.1 aNasr, Vali, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSalehi-Isfahani, Djavad, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079133440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363781840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503637818423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503637818/original  a978-3-11-079133-4  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles